eraQuotes.dead-ball: "They don't call it the House That Ruth Built for nothing."
eraQuotes.murderers-row: "I'd rather be lucky than good." — Lefty Gomez
eraQuotes.dimaggio: "I want to thank the Good Lord for making me a Yankee." — Joe DiMaggio
eraQuotes.mantle-maris: "If I had played my career hitting singles like Pete, I'd wear a dress." — Mickey Mantle
eraQuotes.lean-years: "It's déjà vu all over again." — Yogi Berra
eraQuotes.bronx-zoo: "The straw that stirs the drink." — Reggie Jackson
eraQuotes.mattingly: "I didn't come to New York to be a star. I brought my star with me." — Don Mattingly
eraQuotes.dynasty: "In my dreams, I never let the boys down." — Derek Jeter
eraQuotes.modern: "I tip my cap and call the Yankees my daddy." — Pedro Martinez, 2004

onThisDate.text: Yankees christen Yankee Stadium with a win — Babe Ruth hits the first homer
Wally Pipp sits out with a headache — Lou Gehrig begins his 2,130-game streak
Babe Ruth hits home run #60, a record that stands for 34 years
Lou Gehrig delivers his 'Luckiest Man' farewell speech at Yankee Stadium
Joe DiMaggio begins his 56-game hitting streak
DiMaggio's 56-game hitting streak is stopped in Cleveland
Don Larsen throws a perfect game in World Series Game 5
Roger Maris hits home run #61, breaking Ruth's single-season record
Mickey Mantle's #7 is retired at Yankee Stadium
Reggie Jackson hits three home runs in World Series Game 6 — 'Mr. October'
The Pine Tar Game — George Brett's home run is initially called out
Jim Abbott throws a no-hitter despite being born without a right hand
Yankees win the World Series for the first time since 1978 — the Dynasty begins
David Wells throws a perfect game against the Twins
David Cone throws a perfect game on Yogi Berra Day
Yankees beat the Mets in the Subway Series for their 3rd straight title
Derek Jeter's walk-off homer in Game 4 of the World Series — 'Mr. November'
The heartbreaking Game 7 loss to Arizona — the Dynasty ends
The final game at the original Yankee Stadium
Yankees win World Series #27, the first in the new Yankee Stadium
Mariano Rivera breaks the all-time saves record (602)
Mariano Rivera's final game — a tearful exit from the mound
Derek Jeter's walk-off single in his final Yankee Stadium game
Aaron Judge hits home run #62, breaking the AL record
Nolan Ryan throws his 7th no-hitter — but Don Mattingly's Yankees were the opponent
Yankees rally from 3-1 deficit to beat the Braves and win the World Series
Mickey Mantle wins the Triple Crown, leading the Yankees to a World Series title
MLB retires Jackie Robinson's #42 league-wide — Rivera grandfathered in
Thurman Munson tragically dies in a plane crash — the Bronx mourns
Joe DiMaggio extends his hitting streak to 45 games vs. the Red Sox
Babe Ruth's final appearance at Yankee Stadium — his number 3 is retired
Bucky Dent's three-run homer lifts the Yankees over the Red Sox in a one-game playoff
Mickey Mantle, Roger Maris, and Bill Skowron hit consecutive homers
Aaron Boone's walk-off homer in Game 7 of the ALCS vs. the Red Sox
The Red Sox complete an unprecedented 3-0 comeback to beat the Yankees in the ALCS
Dwight Gooden throws a no-hitter for the Yankees
Dave Righetti throws a no-hitter on George Steinbrenner's birthday
